<TEXT>
a utility company employee says saving lives 
seems to be a fringe benefit of his job 
in the past three years stan dexter has helped rescued a family 
from a burning home revived a girl suffering from a seizure and 
resuscitated a man who got a 12000volt shock 
it just seems natural dexter said you know what has to be 
done and you go in and do it 
dexter a troubleshooter for the kansas gas and electric co was 
called to investigate a power failure in july in an electrical 
substation in wichita he arrived 12 minutes later to find a man who 
seemed to be dead 
mark albright had gotten past a barbedwire fence and warning 
signs into the substation where he was badly burned by a 
12000volt transformer he was hospitalized for some time but is 
now out and attending physical therapy 
he was pretty much lifeless dexter said he wasnt 
breathing and if he had a pulse i sure couldnt find it 
dexter administered cardiopulmonary resuscitation called rescue 
workers and helped them make their way around dangerous electrical 
equipment before fixing the power outage 
im proud and im glad i was the one who responded to the 
call said dexter who teaches lifesaving techniques at the 
american red cross 
three years ago dexter and two coworkers received citations 
from kgampe for their rescue of a valley center family the american 
red cross gave dexter its highest award for resuscitating 2yearold 
regina charles after she underwent a seizure 
dexter said he loves his job because it allows him to work 
outdoors and meet people saving the occasional life he said is 
just a fringe benefit 
