travel to miami to accompany his wife asela mera hospitalized for 
a broken ankle suffered during a fall in a stairwell 
ive come to continue with the trial which began april 19 and 
demonstrate my innocence blanco said after arriving 
he faces charges of corruption and perjury stemming from his 
alleged sale to the army of millions of dollars worth of vehicles 
clothing and other equipment at inflated prices during his term in 
office which ended in 1986 
shortly after he left office blanco traveled to atlanta for 
heart treatment and was sentenced in absentia to 20 years in prison 
and fined 164 million 
he returned to the dominican republic in november 1988 to appeal 
the sentence and was immediately jailed he was freed on bail july 5 
to accompany his wife to miami 
under dominican law the former president had the right to a new 
trial upon returning to this caribbean nation 
the court has already heard testimony from 78 witnesses and has 
yet to hear testimony from blanco and former armed forces minister 
manuel antonio cuervo gomez who faces the same charges 
two businessmen convicted with blanco in november leonel almonte 
and juan tomas pena valentin are serving 20year prison terms 
